sentences: Yuki Koyanagi (小柳 ゆき, Koyanagi Yuki, born January 26, 1982), is a Japanese pop singer.
She released her first single, 'Anata no kisu o kazoemashô – You Were Mine' on September 15, 1999.
After a break of several years, her latest album 'Sunrise' was released in March 2007.
Yuki sang the American and Japanese National Anthems during the 2006 World Baseball Classic in Tokyo.
She also sang the Japanese National Anthem for an international soccer match between Japan and Trinidad & Tobago in 2006.
